The paper discusses a software platform for symbolic data mining using genetic programming, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Pareto trade-off surfaces, which is a concept commonly used in optimization and control systems (cs.SY), and the use of multiple approaches to discover compact symbolic relationships, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
